  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Empowering Girls through Education</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1.&#xA0;&#xA0;&#xA0;&#xA0;&#xA0;&#xA0; Facilitate lobby and advocacy forums on girl&#x2019;s right to education with educational stakeholders and community members.  
  
2.&#xA0;&#xA0;&#xA0;&#xA0;&#xA0;&#xA0; Train girls as ToTs on life skills education, character development and education performance monitoring.
  
3.&#xA0;&#xA0;&#xA0;&#xA0;&#xA0;&#xA0; Train parents of 9 &#x2013; 13 year on family matters interventions as well as on monitoring of girl&#x2019;s education performance.
  
4.&#xA0;&#xA0;&#xA0;&#xA0;&#xA0;&#xA0; Support adolescent girls with sanitary pads.
  
5.&#xA0;&#xA0;&#xA0;&#xA0;&#xA0;&#xA0; Provision of school scholarship for bright and vulnerable girls for 4 years in high school.
  
6.&#xA0;&#xA0;&#xA0;&#xA0;&#xA0;&#xA0; Train School Management Committee members on school governance, project management, classroom observation and facilitate them develop a School Improvement Plan.  
  
7.&#xA0;&#xA0;&#xA0;&#xA0;&#xA0;&#xA0; Provide teaching and learning materials to schools to ensure proper teaching and learning environment.
  
8.&#xA0;&#xA0;&#xA0;&#xA0;&#xA0;&#xA0; Facilitate quarterly supervisory visits to the schools by the Ministry of Education&#x2019;s Quality Assurance Department.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Girls in Kibera ages 9 &#x2013; 15 years</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Increase proportion of girls completing primary school education and transitioning to secondary education; Enhancing the capacity of primary schools to offer quality primary education.</narrative>
